{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\cf1\b\f0\fs20 You can start and stop logging at runtime, using the \cf2 Logging()\cf1  function. This is useful to catch problems that appear to be happening within a certain section of code, since the log itself can be quite verbose and you might not want to leave it on for all programs and all users.\par
\par
In this example, you can set the logging levels by checking (or unchecking) the values to the left. You can also stop all logging, restart logging, and reset to the INI values by using the buttons at the bottom.\par
\par
You can call a program using the Call Program button in order to generate some data to the logs.\par
